{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"246a1714-b0f1-494d-ae56-0c0f439d6bdb","content":"CLR activation logs track **which .NET runtime gets loaded** — they don't contain application-level exceptions like `NullReferenceException`. They're the wrong diagnostic tool for this issue.\n\n**To diagnose a NullReferenceException, you'd want:**\n- The **stack trace** from the exception\n- The application **source code** around the crash site\n- Optionally, a **crash dump** captured with `dotnet-dump`\n\n**CLR activation logs** are useful when:\n- The wrong runtime version is loaded\n- The runtime fails to load entirely\n- An unexpected .NET 3.5 Feature-on-Demand dialog appears\n\nCould you share the **stack trace** or **source code**? I'd be happy to help track down the null reference. If you do suspect a CLR activation problem (e.g., the app isn't loading the right runtime), I can invoke the CLR activation debugging skill to help with that instead.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d469d5a7-2eab-4301-88e6-61857cd0f806","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking me to analyze CLR activation logs to diagnose a NullReferenceException. However, there are a few issues:\n\n1. CLR activation logs are about runtime loading/selection (which CLR version gets loaded), not about application-level exceptions like NullReferenceException.\n2. The user hasn't provided any logs or code to analyze.\n3. There's a relevant skill \"clr-activation-debugging\" that could help with CLR activation issues.\n\nLet me think about this more carefully. The user says their app crashes with a NullReferenceException and wants me to analyze CLR activation logs. CLR activation logs (produced by mscoree.dll) deal with which runtime version gets loaded - they wouldn't contain information about NullReferenceExceptions. \n\n\nI should check what files are available in the working directory and clarify what the user is actually trying to diagnose, since there might be a mismatch between the symptom (NullReferenceException) and the logs they're pointing me to.","outputTokens":494},"id":"1592b02a-9e81-4ad8-bd36-cbce222e453c","timestamp":"2026-04-04T01:12:38.330Z","parentId":"3d142ead-ad8b-4c44-8c0f-0e666d2c047e"}
